<BR> <HR> <P>
<H3><A NAME=SECTION00052300000000000000>2.2.3 Asking the Translator to Pass Commands to LaTeX</A></H3>
<P>
<A NAME=pass>&#160;</A>
Commands that should be passed on to LaTeX for processing because
there is no direct translation to HTML may be specified in the <tt> 
.latex2html-init</tt>
file as input to the <tt> <code>process_commands_in_tex</code></tt>
subroutine.
The format is the same as that for specifying commands to be ignored.
Here is an example:
<PRE>&amp;process_commands_in_tex (&lt;&lt;_RAW_ARG_CMDS_);
fbox # {}
framebox # [] # [] # {}
&lt;add your commands here&gt;
_RAW_ARG_CMDS_
</PRE>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Arndt Koester <BR>
Fri May 12 14:23:56 MESZ 1995</I>
