</DOCHDR>
<TITLE>NCSA httpd: FAQ</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="icon.gif"> Frequently Asked Questions</H1>

<H2>Basic Q&amp;A</H2>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#whatis">What is NCSA httpd?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#how">How do I install NCSA httpd?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#cgi">What is CGI?</A>
</UL>

<H2>Using the Server</H2>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#forms">How do I create and process forms?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#imagemaps">How do I setup a clickable imagemap?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#users">How do I manage users for authentication?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#wais">How can I perform keyword searches?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#ssi">How do I set up server-side includes?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#more">What else can I do?</A>
</UL>

<H2>Troubleshooting</H2>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#logfiles">My logfiles are not updated anymore...</A>
</UL>

<H2>Other Features</H2>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="#hidden">Can I have hidden variables in forms?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#multiple">Can I have multiple submit buttons?</A>
<LI> <A HREF="#pgppem">What is PGP/PEM encryption?</A>
</UL>


<HR>
<A NAME="whatis"><H2>What is NCSA httpd?</H2></A>

<A HREF="Overview.html">NCSA httpd</A> is a program to serve information, 
much in the same way that <A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/NCSAMosaicHome.html">NCSA Mosaic </A> is a program to browse information in the 
<A HREF="http://info.cern.ch/">World Wide Web</A>.   <P>

httpd stands for HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) Daemon.
<A HREF="http://info.cern.ch/hypertext/WWW/Protocols/HTTP/HTTP2.html">HTTP</A>
is a protocol with the lightness and speed necessary for a distributed
collaborative hypermedia information system.<P>

<A NAME="how"><H2>How do I install NCSA httpd?</H2></A>

Read documentation on <A HREF="setup/Install.html">NCSA httpd Installation</A>.  <P>


<A NAME="cgi"><H2>What is CGI?</H2></A>

CGI stands for Common Gateway Interface.  You can read an <A 
HREF="/cgi/intro.html">introduction</A> and an <A HREF="/cgi/">overview</A>. <P>

<HR>
<A NAME="forms"><H2>How do I create and process forms?</H2></A>

First, read <A 
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/fill-out-forms/overview.html">
a tutorial on creating forms</A>.  Then, in order to handle the output from
your forms, read <A HREF="/cgi/forms.html">how CGI supports forms</A>.  <P>

<A NAME="imagemaps"><H2>How do I setup a clickable imagemap?</H2></A>

Read the <A HREF="setup/admin/Imagemap.html">
documentation on the imagemap script</A> and a 
<A HREF="http://wintermute.ncsa.uiuc.edu:8080/map-tutorial/image-maps.html">
tutorial</A> on graphical information maps. <P>

<A NAME="users"><H2>How do I manage user for authentication?</H2></A>

Read the documentation on <A HREF="setup/admin/UserManagement.html">
managing users</A> and a <A 
HREF="http://wintermute.ncsa.uiuc.edu:8080/auth-tutorial/tutorial.html">
tutorial</A> on user authentication. <P>

<A NAME="wais"><H2>How can I perform keyword searches?</H2></A>

You can use WAIS as a back-end search engine.  Herein, a <A 
HREF="http://wintermute.ncsa.uiuc.edu:8080/wais-tutorial/wais-and-http.html">
tutorial</A> on WAIS and HTTP integration. <P>

<A NAME="ssi"><H2>How do I set up server-side includes?</H2></A>

You can use server-side includes, to provide data to clients on-the-fly.  
For example, the current date or the size or last modification date for a 
file.  Check out a <A 
HREF="http://wintermute.ncsa.uiuc.edu:8080/wais-tutorial/wais-and-http.html">
tutorial</A> on server-side includes. <P>

<A NAME="more"><H2>What else can I do?</H2></A>

Read the complete documentation on <A HREF="setup/admin/Overview.html">
server administration</A> and some provided step-by-step 
<A HREF="http://hoohoo.ncsa.uiuc.edu/docs/tutorials/">tutorials</A>. <P>

<HR>
<A NAME="logfiles"><H2>My logfiles are not updated anymore...</H2></A>

This is probably because you moved them or erased them without restarting
a standalone daemon.  For more information, read the <A 
HREF="http://hoohoo.ncsa.uiuc.edu/docs/setup/admin/Logs.html">
Logfile Management</A> documentation. <P>


<HR>
<A NAME="hidden"><H2>Can I have hidden variables in forms?</H2></A>

Actually this is handled by the browser (e.g. NCSA Mosaic).  In any
case, there is an <A 
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/fill-out-forms/example-13.html">
example with hidden variables</A> in the documentation. <P>

<A NAME="multiple"><H2>Can I have multiple submit buttons?</H2></A>

This is also handled by your browser.  NCSA Mosaic for X (v2.5 soon to be released)
will have support for multiple submit buttons.  See an <A 
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/fill-out-forms/example-14.html">
example</A> to learn how to use them. <P>

<A NAME="pgppem"><H2>What is PGP/PEM encryption?</H2></A>

PGP and PEM are programs to allow you and a second party to communicate in a
way which does not allow third parties to read your messages.  For more 
information, there is a <A HREF="PEMPGP.html">PGP/PEM FAQ</A>. <P>

<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="back.gif">Return to the
Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
