<TITLE>Why NCSA httpd?</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="icon.gif"> Why NCSA httpd?</H1>

<HR> <P>
Here is a list of the server's features. Follow the links to read
about them and see demonstrations of their use. <P>
<HR> <P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="Lightweight.html">Low impact</A> <P>
    Designed to be small and fast. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Compat.html">Compatibility</A> <P>
    Works with most HTTP/0.9 and HTTP/1.0 browsers. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Directory.html">Unified directory structure</A> <P>
    Documents are served from a single virtual directory. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Indexes.html">Directory indexes</A> <P>
    Tell users what is in your directories. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="UserDirectories.html">User supported directories</A> <P>
    Allow users to have their own HTML directories. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Scripts.html">Server scripts</A> <P>
    Customize your server to execute searches and handle HTML forms. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Security.html">Security</A> <P>
    Limit access to certain directories of your server. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="Includes.html">Server side include files</A> <P>
    Include the output of commands or other files in your HTML documents. <P>
</UL>
<HR> <P>
If you are interested, here is a <A HREF="VersionHist.html">version
history</A> of past releases. <P>
<HR> <P>

<A HREF="../Overview.html"><IMG SRC="back.gif"> Return to the
overview</A>. <P>
</DOC>
