<TITLE>NCSA httpd Directory</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> Directory directive</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

Directory is a <A HREF="SectionDirectives.html">sectioning
directive</A> which controls the directory to which access control directives
apply.  <P>

<HR>
<H2>Scope</H2>

This directive applies only to the Global ACF. All <A
HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directives</A> in the Global
ACF must be contained in a Directory section. <P>

<HR>

<H2>Syntax</H2>

Opening Directive: <P>

<CODE>&lt;Directory dir&gt;</CODE> <P>

<CODE>dir</CODE> is the absolute pathname of the directory you are
protecting. If you are using NCSA httpd 1.2 or later, this can also be
a <a href="../MatchExp.html">wildcard expression</a> of a set of
directories you wish to protect.<P>

Closing directive: <P>

<CODE>&lt;/Directory&gt;</CODE> <P>
<HR>

<H2>Example</H2>

<PRE>
&lt;Directory /u/Web&gt;
Options None
&lt;/Directory&gt;
</PRE>

The directives contained within the Directory section above would only
apply to the server directory /u/Web. <P>
<HR> <P>

<A HREF="Overview.html#Directives"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to access
configuration overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
