<TITLE>Directory Indexing</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="icon.gif"> Directory Indexing</H1>

<HR> <P>

NCSA httpd allows you to create HTML catalogs of your directories, in
order to tell users what's in them.  <P>
<HR> <P>

For instance, on hoohoo, I have a directory containing some neat
pictures, and I've written a small index for it. <A
HREF="raytraced/">Have a look</A>. <P>

I have another directory whose contents are constantly changing. I
don't really want to write and maintain an index. In this case, httpd
will generate an <A HREF="star_trek/">index</A> of the directory for
me when a user requests the directory. I can configure httpd to ignore
certain files, to give a certain icon for certain files, to place a
short description after file names, and include either an HTML or
plaintext README which tells people what is in the directory.<P>

<HR> <P>

<A HREF="Features.html"><IMG SRC="back.gif"> Return to the features
list</A>. <P>
</DOC>
