<TITLE>User Supported Directories</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="icon.gif"> User Supported Directories</H1>

<HR> <P>

NCSA httpd allows you to let users make their own directories
available for HTTP access, without your having to create links to
them. Of course, you can limit what the users can do from their
directories for security reasons. <P>

<HR> <P>

For instance, take a look at this picture of the <A
HREF="/~robm/ssf.jpg">space station freedom</A> from Rob's home
directory. <P>

