<TITLE>Configuration of NCSA httpd</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="icon.gif"> Configuration</H1>

Configuration means customizing httpd's configuration files to reflect
your system and how httpd should act on your system. <P> 

Please read this <A HREF="ConfigureInfo.html">general
information</A> which applies to all of httpd's configuration
files.<P>

<HR> <P>

There are three main configuration files you must edit. <P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="httpd/Overview.html">Server Configuration</A> <P>
    Technical aspects of server operation. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="srm/Overview.html">Resource Configuration</A> <P>
    Document and script locations and aliases. <P>
<LI> <A HREF="access/Overview.html">Access Control</A> <P>
    Control which clients access certain directories, and which features
    are available in different directories. <P>
</UL>

