<TITLE>NCSA httpd ServerRoot</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> ServerRoot directive</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

The ServerRoot <A HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directive</A>
sets the directory in which httpd lives.  <P>

Upon startup, httpd expects to find the Server Configuration File as
conf/httpd.conf in the ServerRoot directory.  <P>

Other Server Configuration directives may use this directory to give
relative paths for locations of files. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>ServerRoot dir</CODE> <P>

Where <CODE>dir</CODE> is an absolute path of a directory on your
server machine. <P>

Only one ServerRoot directive is allowed in the server configuration
file. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Default</H2>

If you do not specify a ServerRoot, httpd assumes: <P>

<CODE>ServerRoot /usr/local/etc/httpd</CODE> <P>

<HR>
<H2>Examples</H2>

<CODE>ServerRoot /usr/local/httpd</CODE> <P>

This would set ServerRoot to the directory /usr/local/httpd. <P>

<CODE>ServerRoot /web1/http</CODE> <P>

This would set ServerRoot to /web1/http. <P>

<HR>
<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to Server
Configuration File Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
