<TITLE>NCSA httpd Limit</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> Limit directive</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

Limit is a <A HREF="SectionDirectives.html">sectioning
directive</A> which controls which clients can access a directory.<P>

<HR>
<H2>Scope</H2>

This directive applies to both the global and per-directory ACFs. <P>

<HR>

<H2>Syntax</H2>

Opening Directive: <P>

<CODE>&lt;Limit meth1 meth2 ... methn&gt;</CODE> <P>

Each <CODE>meth</CODE> is one of the following methods: <P>
<UL>
<LI> <CODE>GET</CODE> <P>

    Allows clients to retrieve documents and execute scripts. <P>

<LI> <CODE>PUT</CODE> <P>

    Not Implemented. <P>
<LI> <CODE>POST</CODE> <P>

    Not fully implemented. Currently, allows clients to use POST scripts.  <P>
</UL> <P>

Closing directive: <P>

<CODE>&lt;/Limit&gt;</CODE> <P>

Only the following directives are allowed inside Limit sections: <P>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="order.html">order</A>
<LI> <A HREF="deny.html">deny</A>
<LI> <A HREF="allow.html">allow</A>
<LI> <A HREF="require.html">require</A>
</UL>


<HR>

<H2>Example</H2>

<PRE>
&lt;Limit GET&gt;
order deny,allow
deny from all
allow from .ncsa.uiuc.edu
require group sdg
&lt;/Limit&gt;
</PRE>

The only clients allowed to use the <CODE>GET</CODE> method in this
directory must be from ncsa.uiuc.edu, and authenticate to group sdg.
<P>

<HR> <P>

<A HREF="Overview.html#Directives"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to access
configuration overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
<DOC>
