<TITLE>NCSA httpd DefaultIcon</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> DefaultIcon directive</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

This directive specifies what icon should be shown in an automatically
generated directory listing for a file which has no icon information. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>DefaultIcon location</CODE> <P>

<CODE>location</CODE> is the <A
HREF="../admin/AccessingFiles.html#path">virtual path</A> to the icon
on your server. <P>

Only one DefaultIcon directive should appear in the configuration file. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Default</H2>

If no DefaultIcon is present, httpd assumes nothing.

<HR>
<H2>Example</H2>

<CODE>DefaultIcon /icons/unknown.xbm</CODE> <P>

This would cause a file with no icon to be given the icon /icons/unknown.xbm. <P>

<HR> <P>
<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to Resource
Configuration File Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
