<TITLE>NCSA httpd ServerRoot</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> DocumentRoot directive</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

The DocumentRoot <A HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directive</A>
sets the directory from which httpd will serve files.  <P>

If you need to serve files outside this directory, you can use the <A
HREF="Alias.html">Alias</A> directive, or create symbolic links. <P>

This directive affects how you <A
HREF="../admin/AccessingFiles.html">access files on your
server</A>. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>DocumentRoot dir</CODE> <P>

Where <CODE>dir</CODE> is an absolute path of the directory you want
documents to be served from. <P>

Only one DocumentRoot directive is allowed in the server configuration
file. <P>

<HR>
<H2>Default</H2>

If you do not specify a DocumentRoot, httpd assumes: <P>

<CODE>DocumentRoot /usr/local/etc/httpd/htdocs</CODE> <P>

<HR>
<H2>Example</H2>

<CODE>DocumentRoot /home/web</CODE> <P>

This would set DocumentRoot to the directory /home/web. <P>

<HR> <P>
<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to Resource
Configuration File Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
