<TITLE>NCSA httpd Server Configuration File</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> Server Configuration File</H1>

When you unpacked httpd, there should have been a directory called
<CODE>conf</CODE>. In there is a file called
<CODE>httpd.conf-dist</CODE>. This is a template for your server
configuration file. We suggest you use this file only for
reference, and edit the file <CODE>conf/httpd.conf</CODE> as your
server configuration file. <P>

<HR> <P>

Here is a list of the <A
HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directives</A> this file
recognizes. Following the link will give you usage information,
default values, and examples. <P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="ServerType.html">ServerType</A>
<LI> <A HREF="Port.html">Port</A>
<LI> <A HREF="User.html">User</A>
<LI> <A HREF="Group.html">Group</A>
<LI> <A HREF="ServerAdmin.html">ServerAdmin</A>
<LI> <A HREF="ServerRoot.html">ServerRoot</A>
<LI> <A HREF="ServerName.html">ServerName</A>
<LI> <A HREF="TimeOut.html">TimeOut</A>
<LI> <A NAME="sr_dependent" HREF="ErrorLog.html">ErrorLog</A>
<LI> <A HREF="TransferLog.html">TransferLog</A>
<LI> <A HREF="PidFile.html">PidFile</A>
<LI> <A HREF="AccessConfig.html">AccessConfig</A>
<LI> <A HREF="ResourceConfig.html">ResourceConfig</A>
<LI> <A HREF="TypesConfig.html">TypesConfig</A>
<LI> <A HREF="IdentityCheck.html">IdentityCheck</A>
</UL>

