<TITLE>NCSA httpd AuthType</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> AuthType</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

The AuthType <A HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directive</A>
sets the type of authorization used in this directory. <P>
<HR>

<H2>Scope</H2>

This directive applies to both global and per-directory ACFs. <P>

This directive must be accompanied by <A
HREF="AuthName.html">AuthName</A>, <A
HREF="AuthUserFile.html">AuthUserFile</A>, and <A
HREF="AuthGroupFile.html">AuthGroupFile</A> directives in order for
user authentication to work properly. <P>
<HR>

<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>AuthType type</CODE> <P>

<CODE>type</CODE> is the authentication type to use for this
directory. Only <CODE>Basic</CODE> is currently implemented. <P>

<HR>

<H2>Default</H2>

There is no default. <P>

<HR>

<H2>Example</H2>

<CODE>AuthType Basic</CODE> <P>

Sets the authorization type of this directory to <CODE>Basic</CODE>. <P>

<HR> <P>

<A HREF="Overview.html#Directives"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to access
configuration overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>



