<TITLE>NCSA httpd ServerAdmin</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> ServerAdmin directive</H1>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

The ServerAdmin <A HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directive</A>
gives the server your e-mail address. This is so that the server can
give people your address to report error conditions.<P>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>ServerAdmin address</CODE> <P>

Where <CODE>address</CODE> is an e-mail address. <P>

Only one ServerAdmin directive is allowed in the server configuration
file. <P>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Default</H2>

If you do not specify a ServerAdmin, httpd assumes nothing and prints
no address for reporting errors. <P>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Examples</H2>

<CODE>ServerAdmin www@widget.com</CODE> <P>

Errors will have the address www@widget.com as the person to blame. <P>

<HR> <P>
<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to Server
Configuration File Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
