<TITLE>NCSA httpd ServerName</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../icon.gif"> ServerName directive</H1>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Purpose</H2>

The ServerName <A HREF="../ConfigureInfo.html#Directive">directive</A>
sets the hostname httpd should return when creating redirection URLs.
<P>

This directive should be used on systems where
<CODE>gethostbyname</CODE> may not work on the local host, or where
the hostname returned should be a DNS alias such as
<CODE>www.widget.com</CODE>. <P>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Syntax</H2>

<CODE>ServerName FQDN</CODE> <P>

Where <CODE>FQDN</CODE> is the full hostname (including domain name)
to be returned as the server address. <P>

Only one ServerName directive is allowed in the server configuration
file. <P>

<HR> <P>
<H2>Default</H2>

If you do not specify a ServerName, httpd retrieves it through system
calls. <P>


<HR> <P>
<H2>Example</H2>

<CODE>ServerName www.widget.com</CODE> <P>

This would set the server's hostname as www.widget.com, as opposed to
monster.widget.com as would be returned from the gethostname system
call. <P>

<HR> <P>
<A HREF="Overview.html"><IMG SRC="../back.gif">Return to Server
Configuration File Overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
