<TITLE>Get Scripts</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../../icon.gif"> Writing Get Scripts</H1>

Here are detailed instructions for writing GET scripts for NCSA
httpd. Most of these principles apply to POST scripts. <P>

<HR> <P>

<H2>Instructions</H2>

Read each of the following: <P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="args.html">You get your arguments on the
     command line. </A>
<LI> <A HREF="unescape.html">You must unescape the
     arguments yourself.</A>
<LI> <A HREF="envvars.html">The server gives you information about
     itself in the environment</A>
<LI> <A HREF="header.html">Your output must begin with a
     header</A>

</UL>

<HR> <P>

All of these examples come with the distribution of NCSA httpd, in the
<CODE>htbin</CODE> directory. <P>

For an example of using GET scripts to serve and respond to HTML
&lt;ISINDEX&gt; documents, see the <A
HREF="calendar.txt">source</A> for <CODE>calendar</CODE>.<P>

For an example of using GET scripts to serve and respond to HTML <A
HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/Docs/fill-out-forms/overview.html">form</A>, 
see the source for the <A HREF="jj.txt">Jimmy John's form</A>.
For a simpler example, see the source for the <A
 HREF="query.c.txt">query</A> program. <P>

<HR> <P>

<A HREF="PostScripts.html"><IMG SRC="../../fwd.gif">Writing POST
scripts</A> <P>
<A HREF="../Scripts.html"><IMG SRC="../../back.gif">Return to script
overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B22-214</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA014-000148-B030-183</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://wolf2.mpibpc.gwdg.de:80/HTTPD/setup/admin/script-data/PostScripts.html 134.76.213.25 19970217112100 text/html 1152
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Mon, 17 Feb 1997 11:21:21 GMT
