<TITLE>NCSA httpd environment vars</TITLE>
<H1><IMG SRC="../../icon.gif"> Environment Variables</H1>

httpd makes certain server information available to scripts for use.
<P>

<HR>

The following environment variables are defined when httpd is
executing a script. <P>

<UL>
<LI> <CODE>SERVER_ROOT</CODE> <P>

    The setting of <A
    HREF="../../httpd/ServerRoot.html">ServerRoot</A>. <P>


<LI> <CODE>DOCUMENT_ROOT</CODE> <P>

    The setting of <A
    HREF="../../srm/DocumentRoot.html">DocumentRoot</A>. <P>

<LI> <CODE>SERVER_NAME</CODE> <P>

    Formatted as <CODE>name:port</CODE>, where <CODE>name</CODE> is
    the <A HREF="../../httpd/ServerName.html">ServerName</A> and
    <CODE>port</CODE> is the <A HREF="../../httpd/Port.html">Port</A>.
    <P>

<LI> <CODE>REMOTE_HOST</CODE> <P>

    The name of the remote host accessing your script. <P>

</UL>

<HR>  <P>

<A HREF="header.html"><IMG SRC="../../fwd.gif">Move on to outputting a
header</A> <P> 

<A HREF="GetScripts.html"><IMG SRC="../../back.gif">Return to GET
script overview</A> <P>

<ADDRESS>httpd@ncsa.uiuc.edu</ADDRESS>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT08-B22-218</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA014-000148-B031-17</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://wolf2.mpibpc.gwdg.de:80/HTTPD/setup/admin/script-data/header.html 134.76.213.25 19970217112201 text/html 1507
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
