<HEAD>



<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->



<TITLE>News To Use: 4 Your Information </TITLE>



<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->



</HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif" LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<img src="images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>



<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br>



<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<!-------------------------------------------------------------->



<Font size=+1>



<IMG ALIGN=right SRC="images/icons/fyi.gif" width=76 height=76 border=0 hspace=10><b>



<!---------- Begin Page Title ---------------->



<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=10  height=1>



News To Use: 4 Your Information



<!---------- End Page Title ---------------->



</B></Font>



<HR>



<UL>



<li><b>Lotto Numbers</b><br>



Get the latest winning numbers from the <a href="http://www.calottery.com/">California Lottery </a> right here. Also, watch 'The Big Spin' on KRON-TV every Saturday at 6:30 p.m.<p>



<li><b>Daybreak - Web Page of the Day</b><br>

<i>Week of January 20, 1996</i><p>



Monday, 1/20: The Presidential Inauguration<br>

The official site of the Inauguration.  All the information about the ceremony, parade, galas and more.<br>              

<a href="http://www.inaugural97.org/">http://www.inaugural97.org/</a><p>



Tuesday, 1/21: Oakland International Airport<br>

Everything you need to know about the Oakland Airport. The Airlines, terminal maps, ground transportation, lost and found, and more. <br>    

<a href="http://www.flyoakland.com/index.html">http://www.flyoakland.com/index.html</a><p>

     

Wednesday, 1/22: Super Bowl Hosts<br>

New Orleans is the host of the Super Bowl for the 8th time. A listing of events, media coverage, and a visitors guide to the city. <br>

<a href="http://www.superbowlhost.org:80/">http://www.superbowlhost.org:80/</a><p>



Thursday, 1/23: Miraloma Elementary School<br>

A San Francisco Elementary School on the slopes of Mt. Davidson. Check out their Creative Arts, Performing Arts, Computer and Reading Programs and information on their African Museum. <br>

<a href="http://nisus.sfusd.k12.ca.us/schwww/sch722/miralomahome.html">http://nisus.sfusd.k12.ca.us/schwww/sch722/miralomahome.html</a><p>



Friday, 1/24: Peninsula Access For Dogs<br>

Information on open space and parks land on the Peninsula where you can take your dog.  Find out about new laws, trail etiquette and other dog issues.<br>

<a href="http://www.rahul.net/prusik/pads/">http://www.rahul.net/prusik/pads/</a><p>



<li><b>Travinfo</b><br>

Travinfo is designed to give you up-to-the-minute information on drivng conditions in the Bay Area from a variety of sources such as roadway sensors, closed circuit television and CHP reports. Call 817-1717 (you don't need an area code). The service is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week.<p>



<li><b>Domestic Violence Multilingual Hotline</b><br>

A 24-hour hotline number with multilingual staff members is available to Asian victims of domestic violence. The number is (415) 751-0880. Staff members speak 24 different Asian languages and dialects.<p>  



<li><b>Domestic Abuse Hotline</b><br>

If you find yourself in a dangerous situation because of an abusive relationship, there is a number you can call for help. Counseling and referrals are available at the Domestic Abuse Hotline by dialing toll-free 1-800-799-SAFE.<p>



<li><b>San Francisco SPCA</b><br>

If you'd like information about adopting a pet, call the San Francisco SPCA at (415) 554-3000.<p>



<li><b>Van Pool</b><br>

To locate a van pool near you or to start one up, call 1-800-755-POOL.<p>



<LI><b>Blood Banks Need Donors</b><br>

Blood banks throughout the Bay Area say blood shortages are now becoming a year-round

problem. If you want to find out the nearest blood donation center near you, call toll-free at 1-800-864-4835. To donate, you have to be 17 years old, healthy, and weigh a minimum of 110 pounds. <BR><br>



</ul>



