<i>Updated: Tuesday 21 January, 9:27am pst</i><p>
<p><h2>Bet On Wet</h2>
<p>
Another in a series of storms has signalled a right
turn off the Pacific and is crusing toward a close
encounter of the wet kind by tonight, promising more
rain through Wednesday.  Overnight snow will total as
much as a foot of powder above 6000ft. near Tahoe,
with snow levels down to 5000ft in the Central Sierra;
3000ft. feet up north.
Tim Haddix updates this discussion shortly.  Steve Raleigh,
prancing about on a wounded ankle, has reported to the
sick bay, so I'll be BACK at the helm of the good ship
WeatherCenter tonight, beginning on First4News at 4pm,
laden with coffee strong enough to walk on.<p>
<b>Wakefully,</B><br>
<b>hackney</B>
