<H1>



<!---------- BEGIN PAGE TITLE ---------------->



What's Hot in the Bay Area



<!---------- END PAGE TITLE ---------------->



</H1>



<HR>



<br>



<b>Find out the hottest events taking place around the Bay Area.</b><p>



</center>



<TABLE width=95%>



<hr>



<TR>



<!-- Enter text ----------------------------------------------------------->



<blockquote>



<b>Lasers, Light & Color</b><br>

<i>Ongoing</i><p>

New series of hands-on and interactive exhibits. Explore and understand rainbows, shadows and reflections, and innovative uses of light.<p>

The Tech Museum of Innovation<br>

145 W. San Carlos Street<br>

San Jose<br>

For more information, call (408) 272-7150<p>



<hr width=30%><br>



<b>The Cryptogram</b><br>

<i>Through February 9</i><p>

West Coast premiere of two-time Pulitzer Prize-winner David Mamet's drama about a disintegrating marriage and the betrayal of a friend seen through the eyes of a lonely and fearful young boy.<p>

Magic Theatre - Bldg. D<br>

Fort Mason Center, San Francisco<br>

For more information, call (415) 441-8822.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>Margaret Cho, Scott Silverman</b><br>

<i>January 15-19</i><p>

Punchline - Sacramento<br>

2100 Arden Way, Suite 225<br>

Two shows Friday & Saturday at 9pm and 11pm...Tickets are $12.<br>

One show Sunday at 9pm...Tickets are $10.<br>

For more information, call (916) 925-8500.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>On Angels' Wings</b><br>

<i>January 19</i><p>

The Bay Area Filipino community hosts a performance of the Loboc Children's Choir, an award-winning ensemble of 30 children from the island of Bohol, who sing Filipino folk, classics, and contemporary songs.<p>

Cowell Theatre<br>

Fort Mason Center, San Francisco<br>

3pm & 7pm<br>

Tickets: $15, $10 seniors & under 18<br>

For more information, call (415) 436-9711.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>Paramount Movie Classics</b><br>

<i>January 24-March 22</i><p>

Winter 1997 Movie Schedule:<br>

Casablanca - Friday, January 24 at 8pm<br>

Breakfast At Tiffany's - Saturday, February 15 at 8pm<br>

Sunset Boulevard - Friday, February 21 at 8pm<br>

From Russia With Love - Saturday, March 1 at 8pm<br>

To Catch A Thief - Friday, March 7 at 8pm<br>

Easter Parade - Saturday, March 22 at 8pm<p>

Paramount Theatre<br>

2025 Broadway<br>

Oakland, CA 94612<br>

General admission tickets: $5.00    <br>

For more information, call (510) 465-6400.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>Luthor Vandross, The Braxtons</b><br>

<i>January 28 & 29</i><p>

Paramount Theatre<br>

Oakland<br>

8pm<br>

Advance ticket price: $50.00 res. Tickets available at all Bass Ticket Centers.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>B.B. King</b><br>

<i>February 7</i><p>

Paramount Theatre<br>

Oakland<br>

8pm<br>

Advance ticket price: $32.50 res. Tickets available at all Bass Ticket Centers.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>Teen City: A Festival of Plays By Youth</b><br>

<i>February 9</i><p>

Learn how youth see San Francisco in the 2nd annual festival of plays created by young people growing up in the city.<p>

Bayfront Theater<br>

Fort Mason Center, San Francisco<br>

2pm<br>

Admission is free.<br>

For recorded information, call (415) 285-1720.<p>



<HR width=30%><br>



<b>Sybase Open</b><br>

<i>February 10-16</i><p>

Three of tennis' biggest stars -- Andre Agassi, Pete Sampras and Michael Chang -- bring their superb play to the 1997 Sybase Open. This is the Bay Area's premiere tournament for men's professional tennis and is the kick-off North American event on the worldwide ATP tour. Sampras is the defending Sybase Open champion, Agassi seeks his fourth Sybase Open title, while Chang returns to seek a third title in the Bay Area.<p>

San Jose Arena<br>

Individual tickets: $15-$100. All 13 sessions: $350-$395. Four-session packages and group tickets available.<br>

For more information, call (408) ACE-2121<p>



<hr width=30%><br>



<b>Celebration of the Black Dance & Music Experience</b><br>

<i>February 22 & 23</i><p>

The Wajumbe Cultural Institution's annual historical journey in music and dance from Africa to the Caribbean, South America, and the United States. An African Bazaar & Food Tasting takes place before each performance.<p>

Bayfront Theater<br>

Fort Mason Center, San Francisco<br>

Concert: Sat 8pm, Sun 3pm<br>

Bazaar: Sat 7pm, Sun 2pm<br>

Tickets: $14, $12 advance/seniors/students<br>

For more information, call (415) 563-3519.<p>



<br>



