<b>Healthbeat Flash: Prozac</b><br>
<font=2><i>Aired: December 12, 1996</b></font><p>

There is an herbal alternative to prozac to treat depression. Health food stores can barely keep their shelves stocked with Saint John's Wart, also known as hypericum. Chemicals in the herbal extract appear to lift moods without all the bad side effects of prozac, which is the most common anti-depressant on the market. Unlike prozac though, hypericum has yet to be clinically tested.<p>

