<HTML>
<HEAD>


<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>Welcome to KRON Online
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="nc4/images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">




<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>
<center>
<Img border=0 Src="images/four.gif" Height=121 Width=90><br>
</center>
<br><br>

<br>
<img src="images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>

<center>
<img src="images/mastii.gif" height=60 Width=414 border=0>
</center>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote>
<H3>
<!-----------------------Begin Story Title --------------------------->
Welcome to KRON-TV's Family of Web Sites
<!-----------------------End Story Title --------------------------->
</H3></blockquote><blockquote>
<BR>
All of us at KRON and Chronicle Broadcasting are looking forward to the new challenges and exciting opportunities the World Wide Web is presenting media companies. 
<p>
KRON-TV, part of the Chronicle Publishing Company, is in the midst of an era in which the way people receive information is changing dramatically. Bay Area viewers have selected KRON as their News and Information Leader. We feel fortunate to be a part of the Bay Area's rich history and want to be your link to the future.
<p>
We've been part of the San Francisco Bay Area since 1865, when two teenage brothers named de Young began publishing a one-page circular and distributing it to theater-goers. At that time, circulation numbered in the hundreds. In 1949, KRON-TV went on the air, reaching approximately 20,000 households. Today, KRON reaches more than two million households in the Bay Area. Although our focus is regional, the World Wide Web will allow us to connect with audiences far beyond Northern California. 
<p>
With the launch of our family of Web sites, we are able to reach out to our viewers, our community, and to a new global audience. Let us know what you think of our sites. Keep us informed on what you want from our sites and how we can make it more friendly and useful for you. 
<p>
As a user of the Web, you know this interactive environment will enable you to add your creative energies to the development of these sites. We will be listening because we know we have a unique opportunity to learn.
<p>
We are really looking forward to hearing from you.
<p>
<b>Amy McCombs</b><br>
President and CEO, Chronicle Broadcasting<p>
<br>
</BLOCKQUOTE></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign=top>
