<HEAD>
<TITLE>WeatherCenter4 - Western View</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000"
BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">
<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>
<!----------- Page Image -------------->
<img src="images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129
border=0>
<!----------- End Image -------------->
<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>
</td>
<td valign=top>
<blockquote>
<h1>
<!---------- Begin Page Title ---------------->
Western View
<!---------- End Page Title ---------------->
</h1></blockquote>
<center>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=400  height=1>
<img src="images/WEST-SAT.JPG" width=300 height=226
border=2><p>
</center><blockquote>
<i>Updated: Tuesday 21 January, 9:27am pst</i><p>
<!---------- Begin text ---------------->
<p><h2>Baby, The Rain Must Fall</h2><p>
...and, as the great and good Glenn Yarborough proclaimed,
the wind must blow--as it will over the next 24 hours
in advance of another storm due off the Pacific by tonight.
The storm, tropical in nature, will provide more rain
than this last system and, once more, favor the south
bay.  Further, echoes should begin to light up first over
the Monterey Bay area before the rain begins in earnest
over San Francisco.  And, of course, we still have 
residual moisture from the exiting storm to deal with
during the daytime today (Tuesday).  All in all, a wet
week ahead, with something of a break promised by Thursday
afternoon.  We shall see.  Steve Raleigh's on the mend,
nursing an ankle he sprained while springing to fetch
the weather wand, so I'll be more than pleased to make
an evening appearance on the nighttime news, if only to
try to get a signed photo of Gary Radnich.
<p>
<b>Wakefully,</B><br>
<b>hackney</b>
<!---------- End text ---------------->
</blockquote>
</center>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign=top>
<a href="home.html"><img src="../images/back.gif" width=82
height=36 border=0
vspace=2></a> <br>
</td>
<td valign=top><center><a href="../home.html"><img
src="../images/nc4_header_sm.gif"
border=0 width=156 height=39></a> <br><br>
