<HEAD>



<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->



<TITLE> New Liposuction Method </TITLE>



<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->



</HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../../images/background.gif" LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left border=0>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<img src="../images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>



<img src="../../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br><br>



<br>



<img src="../../images/greydot.gif" width=150 height=1>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<blockquote>



<font size=+3><b>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title --------------------------->



New Liposuction Method 



<!-----------------------End Story Title --------------------------->



</b></font><br>



<font size=2><i>



Aired: 



<!-- Enter date aired -->



November 4, 1996



<!-------------------->



</i></font><p>



<!-----------------------Begin text --------------------------->



<b>Diet and exercise are the best ways of reducing your risk of heart disease and, of course, of losing weight. But when it comes to reducing fat, some people want faster results. Now they have a new option:  a new method of liposuction using ultrasound.</b><p>



The Wayne Bates of today is quite different to the old Wayne. "Basically I got tired of looking at myself with two stomachs, and clothing was very difficult to buy," he says.<p>



<IMG SRC="liposuction_images/1.jpeg" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 VSPACE=10 HEIGHT="120" WIDTH="160" BORDER=1>



So Wayne tried a new form of liposuction in which ultrasonic sound waves liquefy the fat, which is then removed. <p>



Cosmetic surgeon Dr. Patrick Maxwell says only the fat is affected, "And rather than sucking fat out, the fat is turned into a liquid and the liquid then gently comes out of the body." <p>



<IMG SRC="liposuction_images/2.jpeg" ALIGN=right HSPACE=10 VSPACE=10 HEIGHT="120" WIDTH="160" BORDER=1>



Dr. Maxwell says it's more gentle than the regular liposuction, causes less bleeding, and removes more fat. "More precise fat can be removed," he adds. <p>



Compare Wayne "Before" to "After" he had twenty-five pounds removed. <p>



"I'd recommend it to anyone," remarks Wayne. "There's just nothing to it." <p>



<b>Of course, liposuction is not cheap, and there are no guarantees that you won't put back on however much weight you have taken off. The only way to be sure you keep those pounds off is the old-fashioned 

way; by watching what you eat and keeping physically active. And if you do choose liposuction, be sure to find a reputable surgeon.</b><p>



<!------------------------------------------------->



</BLOCKQUOTE></td>



</tr>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<a href="../home.html"><img src="../../images/back.gif" width=82 height=36 border=0 vspace=2></a><br>



</td>



<td valign=top><center><a href="../../home.html"><img src="../../images/nc4_header_sm.gif" border=0 width=156 height=39></a><br><br>



<hr>



<font size=2>Copyright &copy; 1996 <a href="http://www.kron.com"><b>KRON-TV</b></a>. All rights reserved.</font>



