Posted by <a href="mailto:jet@value.net">James Tunnell</a> on January 20, 1997 at 11:46:33:<p>
On March 17, 1937, Amelia Earhart took off from what is now Earhart Field in Oakland and disappeared somewhere over the Pacific Ocean. On March 17th of this year, Linda Finch, a Bay Area pilot will try to complete history flying a twin engine Lockheed Electra 10E exactly like the one flown by Earhart into the pages of history. Finch plans to leave on the same day as Earhart and trace the same course. Finch, unlike Earhart will have the advantage of certain modern technologies including global-positioning satellites, long-range VHF radio communications, and a digital camera and satellite transceiver to send messages and "live" images to viewers of the Internet. March 17th is also St. Patrick's Day. With any luck Finch will suceed where Earhart died trying.
<br>
