<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=+2><b>LISA ARGEN</b></FONT><BR>
<b>Meteorologist</b><p>

Lisa Argen joined KRON-TV as staff meteorologist in June 1995. <BR>
<BR>
Prior to KRON, Argen worked at WFLD/Fox 32 in Chicago, where she was
meteorologist
for the weekday broadcast &quot;Fox News Chicago&quot; since June 1993.
Before that, she was a meteorologist at WBIR/Action 10 News in Knoxville,
Tenn., where she worked on morning, noon and weekend morning news shows
from June 1991 to June 1993. Prior, she was a meteorology assistant at WGRZ
Channel 2 in Buffalo, N.Y. from December 1990 to May 1991. <BR>
<BR>
Argen earned the National Weather Association Seal of Approval in July 1994.
She received a Certificate of Broadcast Meteorology from Mississippi State
University in Spring 1992, after graduating from the University of Notre
Dame with a B.A. in Communications and Theatre. </BLOCKQUOTE>
