<HEAD>





<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->

    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Susan Blake

</TITLE>

<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->



</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"

LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">







<table align=left  border=0>

<tr>

<td valign=top>



<img src="images/blake.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>

<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br><br>



<br>

<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



</td>

<td valign=top>







<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<Font Size=+2><b>SUSAN BLAKE</b></font><br>

<b> Anchor of "Daybreak" and "Midday" reporter for "First 4 News"</b><p>



Susan Blake joined KRON-TV in January 1990 as weekday anchor of NewsCenter 4's "Daybreak" at 6:00 a.m. and "Midday" at 11:30 a.m. on Channel 4.  She provides news reports for "First 4 News" on weekdays at 4:00 p.m. on Channel 4. <p>



Blake came to KRON from KXTV in Sacramento, where she anchored the evening news.  While at KXTV, she received a "Best of the West" award for her series on business development in California's Capitol.  Prior, she anchored and reported for Sacramento's KOVR-TV.  Her duties as a reporter at KOVR led Blake on assignments to Japan, India, Israel, and Alaska.  In addition, she moderated KOVR's "News Conference 13," a weekly talk show addressing current events and timely issues.<p>



In Sacramento, she served on the Board of Directors of Big Brothers/ Big Sisters and was named Honorary Big Sister of the Year for 1983 to 1984.  Her weekly "Waiting Child" segments on KXTV, which profiled children in hopes of matching them with Big Brothers and Sisters, remain a source of pride for Blake.  She also served on the Board of the Kaplan Foundation for autistic children and the AID to AIDS advisory committee.<p>



A native of Kansas, Blake received a B.S. in Journalism from the University of Kansas.  She enjoys snow skiing, backpacking, hiking, running and cycling.<BR>



</BLOCKQUOTE>

<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->





</td>

</tr>

