<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Claudia Cowan
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/cowan.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>

<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<Blockquote>
<Font Size=+2><b>CLAUDIA COWAN</b></font><br>
<b>General Assignment Reporter</b><p>

Claudia Cowan joined KRON as an update anchor in May 1995.  Five months later, 
she was promoted to general assignment reporter for "NewsCenter 4 Nightbeat" at 
11:00 p.m.<p>

Prior to joining KRON, Cowan worked as a reporter/anchor at KOVR-TV in 
Sacramento since 1989.  From 1986 to 1989, she was reporter/weekend anchor at 
KMST-TV, the CBS affiliate in Monterey, Calif.  Her first television job was at
Los 
Angeles station KTTV, where she was desk assistant from 1985 to 1986.<p>

Cowan earned a Bachelor of Arts Degree in English from the University of 
California, Los Angeles (UCLA) in 1985.<p>

Born in Los Angeles, Cowan grew up in Chicago, Los Angeles and Colorado 
Springs, where she went to boarding school.  She is the daughter of actress
Barbara 
Rush and publicist Warren Cowan, founder of Rogers & Cowan.<p>    

</blockquote>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


