<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<Blockquote>
<Font Size=+2><b>JIM GOLDMAN</b></font><br>
<b>High Tech/Business Reporter</b><p>

With a proven track record as a seasoned reporter of emerging technologies and
multimedia news, Jim Goldman joined KRON as NewsCenter 4 High Tech/Business
Reporter in July 1995.  Based in KRON/BayTV's San Jose NewsCenter, he is also a
reporter on "New Media News," the half-hour technology news program which airs
nationally on the Jones Computer Network and on BayTV, KRON's 24 hour news, talk
and information cable channel<p>
  
Prior to joining KRON, Goldman was anchor and producer of KICU's "Silicon Valley
Business This Week" since September 1993.   Before KICU, he reported a daily
morning business segment on KNTV's "Good Morning San Jose"  from 1989 to 1992. 
At the same time, Goldman also covered the technology industry as a senior
reporter for the San Jose Business Journal.  While earning a degree at Brown
University, Goldman was a reporter for United Press International.<p>

Goldman has been honored for his work by the Peninsula Press Club, receiving a
first place award for Feature Writing.  He has also won six awards from the
Association of Area Business Publications (AABP) for business and technology
reporting.<p>
 
</blockquote>


