<td valign=top>







<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<FONT SIZE=+2><b>JAMES HATTORI</b></FONT><BR>

<b>Weekend Anchor and Weekday Reporter</b><p>



James Hattori joined KRON-TV in May 1996 as weekend co-anchor of NewsCenter4 at 5:00 p.m. and 11:00 p.m. He is also a weekday general assignment reporter for NewsCenter4.<p>



Hattori comes to KRON from CBS News, where was a correspondent since May 1988.  While at CBS, he was assigned to their New York, Tokyo and Dallas bureaus. Some of the major stories he's covered include the Panama invasion, Exxon Valdez oil spill, NASA shuttle missions, Persian Gulf War and the Kobe earthquake. <p>



Prior, he was a reporter at KPRC-TV in Houston from July 1987 to May 1988.  From April 1982 to July 1987, he was a reporter at KING-TV in Seattle.  Before that, he was a reporter at KREM-TV in Spokane, assignment editor at KFMB in San Diego and reporter trainee at KGTV in San Diego. <p>



Hattori is a former national vice-president and active member of the Asian-American Journalists Association. <p>



 </BLOCKQUOTE>

<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->





