<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: John Kessler
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000"
BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/kessler.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>
<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>


</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<Font Size=+2><b>JOHN KESSLER</b></Font><BR>
<b>"Daybreak" Co-Anchor and Reporter</b><p>

"It's the best job there is for someone as curious as I am. I've
traveled to Germany to watch The Wall go down, run river rapids,
piloted a fighter jet, and interviewed some of the world's most
interesting people," says John Kessler, explaining why he first became
a reporter.<P>

Kessler is co-anchor of "Daybreak" weekday at 5:30 a.m. and assignment
reporter for "Midday" weekdays at 11:30 a.m.  He was bureau chief of
KRON's East Bay NewsCenter and co-anchor of "Daybreak" weekends from
January 1994 to March 1996.  Prior, he was weekday co-anchor of
"Daybreak" since November 1992.  He joined KRON-TV as a general
assignment reporter in March 1991, and became NewsCenter 4's Contra
Costa reporter in October 1991.<P>  

Kessler joined KRON after working as a reporter and fill-in anchor at
KOFY-TV in San Francisco.  Prior, he was anchor/managing editor at
KMPH-TV in Fresno.  Kessler's 22 years in the broadcasting industry
include radio anchoring positions at WDRQ in Detroit, WAPE in
Jacksonville, Fla., WAYS in Charlotte, N.C., and KFMB in San Diego.<P>

Kessler received an Emmy nomination from the Northern California
Chapter of the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences in 1993
for "Outstanding Achievement:  News/Information."  He was also
recognized by the Radio and Television News Director's Association in
1991 with the "Best Serious Feature" award for a story on the San Bruno
prison farm.<P>

A graduate of San Diego State University with a bachelor's degree in
journalism, Kessler also studied psychology at North Carolina State
University, and mechanical engineering at Corning College.<P>

An auto racing and water sport enthusiast, Kessler also enjoys running,
fishing, skiing and reading.<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


</td>
</tr>
