<HEAD>


<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Malou Nubla
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000"
BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/nubla.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>

<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<Font Size=+2><b>MALOU NUBLA</b></font><BR>
<b>Traffic Reporter and 24-Hour Update Anchor</b><p>

Malou Nubla joined KRON as TrafficWatch 4 reporter in December 1994. 
Her reports air on "Daybreak" from 5:30 a.m. to 7:00 a.m. on Channel 4
and on "BayTV Morning" at 6:00 a.m. on BayTV, KRON's 24-hour news, talk
and information cable channel.  In addition to providing traffic
reports, Nubla anchors NewsCenter 4's 24-hour updates early weekday
mornings.<P>

Before joining KRON, Nubla worked for Shadow Broadcast Services as a
traffic reporter.  Prior, she worked at KTOP-TV, Channel 11, Oakland's
Government Channel, and was co-host and sports anchor for the weekly
program, "City Speaks." In 1992, she worked at KGO Radio as
programming/listener services coordinator, and soon after became
promotions and community service coordinator.<P>  

Malou received a Bachelor of Arts degree in Broadcast Journalism from
San Francisco State University, where she was president of the Filipino
organization and performed traditional Philippine folk dances.<P> 

She is a Bay Area native and the oldest of four children.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


