<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Karl Sonkin
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/sonkin.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>

<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=+2><b>KARL SONKIN</b></font><br>
<b>General Assignment Reporter</b><p>

Karl Sonkin is an award-winning reporter based in KRON's San Jose news bureau.<p>

Sonkin joined KRON-TV as a general assignment reporter in 1979.  He began his career in journalism working as a "cub" reporter for the Chicago City News Bureau wire service in 1968.  A year later, he went to work for NBC affiliate WDAF in Kansas City.  There, he served as a writer, reporter and anchorman.  In 1971, Sonkin moved on to ABC affiliate WKRC in Cincinnati to become news director as well as news anchor.  Later that year, he came to San Francisco to work as a news producer for CBS affiliate KPIX-TV.  In 1975, Sonkin went to work for ABC affiliate KGO-TV as a writer and reporter.<p>

In 1995, Sonkin won both a local Emmy Award and an Outstanding Achievement Award from the Radio Television News Directors Association for his dramatic live coverage of the tragic Franklin street shooting in San Francisco. He was the first reporter on the scene.<p>

A Chicago native, Sonkin graduated from the University of Illinois in 1966 with a degree in physiology. In his spare time, Sonkin enjoys working with various community and non-profit organizations.<p>													



</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


