<HEAD>


<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Henry Tenenbaum
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/tenenbaum.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>
<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>


</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<Font Size=+2><b>HENRY TENENBAUM</b></font><BR>
<b>Entertainment Reporter</b><p>

Henry Tenenbaum has more than 25 years of journalism experience, from feature
reporter and entertainment critic to assistant news director. He joined
KRON-TV in January 1992 as a NewsCenter 4 reporter, often taking an off-beat
look at the quality of life in California. He also produces &quot;Henry's
Garden,&quot; a weekly garden segment which airs on KRON's weekend
&quot;Daybreak.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Every Thursday night at 9:00 p.m., Tenenbaum hosts &quot;BayTV Prime Talk,&quot;
a weekly one-hour talks show focusing on Bay Area entertainment which airs
on BayTV, KRON's 24-hour news, talk and information cable channel.<BR>
<BR>
Tenenbaum also hosts &quot;Beyond 2000,&quot; a Discovery Channel program
which looks at science and technology in the next millennium. <BR>
<BR>
In the course of his career, Tenenbaum has interviewed well-known figures
ranging from Jimmy Carter to Bruce Springsteen. In his feature reporting,
he has gone wing-walking, sky-diving, scuba diving, and fire-fighting. He
has performed as an extra with the Bolshoi Opera, flown with the Blue Angels
aerobatics team, and climbed caves and cliffs. Tenenbaum has reported from
many interesting and exotic locations, including a pearl farm in Tahiti,
the Tower of London, the gaming tables of Monte Carlo, and the deck of an
aircraft carrier in the mid-Atlantic Ocean.<BR>
<BR>
Tenenbaum started his career as a classical music announcer at WBFO, a public
radio station in Buffalo, New York in 1963. He eventually became music director
and program director at that station. He also worked as an adjunct professor
of communications at the State University of New York at Buffalo. Tenenbaum
began his career in television in 1970 as a reporter/photographer for WKBW-TV
in Buffalo, New York. In 1974, he moved to Washington, D.C., where he traveled
around the country and the world as host of &quot;PM/Evening Magazine.&quot;
He reported human interest and entertainment stories as a correspondent
for NBC's &quot;Today Show&quot; from 1981 to 1983. From 1983 to 1987, Tenenbaum
was an anchorman and correspondent for NBC-owned WRC-TV, where his series
on the AIDS epidemic earned him the Ohio State University National Journalism
Award. Tenenbaum was a syndicated entertainment critic for the Post-Newsweek
stations and WJLA-TV from 1987 to 1990. Before coming to San Francisco from
Washington, D.C. in 1992, Tenenbaum was president of a media consulting
firm.<BR>
<BR>
While at KRON-TV, Tenenbaum has received several local Emmy Awards from
the Northern California Chapter of the National Academy of Television Arts
and Sciences (NATAS). In addition, Tenenbaum received four local Emmy Awards
from the Washington, D.C. Chapter of NATAS for his work as a feature reporter
at WTOP-TV (now W*USA). He also received an Ohio State Award for his report
on AIDS, and the New York State AP award for a documentary he produced on
the Buffalo Police Department.<BR>
<BR>
He attended the State University of New York at Buffalo, where he received
a bachelor of arts degree in English literature and a master of science
degree in educational communications. He also graduated from the New York
University program in radio and television.<BR>
<BR>
Tenenbaum used to devote his spare time to travel and scuba diving. Now
he gardens, plays with computers and repairs leaky taps. </BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


</td>
</tr>
