<!-----------------------Begin Page Title --------------------------->
    <TITLE>NewsCenter 4 People: Marty Uribes
</TITLE>
<!-----------------------End Page Title --------------------------->

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../images/background.gif"
LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top>

<img src="images/uribes.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>
<img src="../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 

<br><br>

<br>
<img src="../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>

</td>
<td valign=top>



<!-----------------------Begin Profile --------------------------->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=+2><b>MARTY URIBES</b></font><br>
<b>General Assignment Reporter</b><p>

Marty Uribes joined KRON-TV in March, 1991 as a general assignment reporter.  She is committed to representing the concerns of the Bay Area's multi-ethnic communities.<p>

She came to KRON from KCBS-TV in Los Angeles, where she had worked as a freelance general assignment reporter in 1990.  Prior, she held a similar position in Los Angeles with KCAL-TV.  Uribes' broadcasting career began in 1979 at KJEO-TV Fresno, Calif., where she worked as a nightside news writer, assistant assignment editor, general assignment reporter covering courts and county governnment, and weekend Newsbriefs anchor.<p>

Uribes was president of the Board of Directors of the California Chicano News Media Association.  She is also a member of the Associated Press/APTRA, the National Association of Hispanic Journalists, San Francisco's Latinos in Communications, and a former member of the Fresno County Bench/Bar/Media.<p>

Uribes received a Bachelor of Arts degree in Journalism from Fresno State University in 1980.  A single parent with a teenage daughter, she hopes to serve as a positive role model for her own child, as well as other young Latinas in the Bay Area.<p>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-----------------------End profile --------------------------->


