Posted by <a href="mailto:stallion@tdl.com">Carlo</a> on January 17, 1997 at 00:39:20:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="524.html">Re: Poor CAL</a> posted by Bill Vinson on January 16, 1997 at 12:41:54:<p>
: <br>: : For one minute lets not think about the 49ers, but about CAL. Seifert did not get screwed here, CAL did! I hope Seifert goes to CAL and they win the national championship and the 9ers go 0-16. That would be justice.<br>: Mariucci certainly sets himself up as a role model ....newspaper today shows him with arms outspread, palms up, with the caption: "What can I do?"  <br>: I have an answer for him:  Go back and listen to what you were saying when you took the job at Cal....you'll find words like commitment...integrity....honor....teacher....long-term, etc.  Apparently, they were just convenient words to use to "market" your image...with no courage of conviction.<br>: Good way to teach your own children!  And what about all the young men in Cal Football who believed in you, looked up to you, and who held very high hopes and dreams that you instilled in them?<p>: "Role Model" Mariucci???  Yeah, for prostitutes, hustlers, and those who sell at<br>: for a price!!<p>: The Univ. of Calif. is far bigger than you are, "Mooch", and while<br>: their football program will suffer for a while because of your lack of integrity and "me first" attitude, it is fortunate<br>: that they learned quickly what a shallow, self-centered person you are! <p>What kind of a moron are you pal? As if you wouldn't take the job right. Oh yeah, you would stay at Cal and get your ass kicked up and down the field by Stanford every year. I believe you, I'm sure that if you had the chance to coach the finest franchise in history and make three times more money you would stay at Cal. Also I'm pretty sure the players understand his departure they are grown men you know. I think you need to understand that the average American is out to do what ever it takes to make life better for them and their families and I don't think there's anything wrong with that! Wake up pal!!
<br>
