Posted by carlo on January 17, 1997 at 09:55:03:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="532.html">Mariucci</a> posted by Chris on January 17, 1997 at 08:25:05:<p>
: Listen Carlo, if you want to take a bottom line approach on this then yeah the decision is a no brainer. Anyone in the business would have done the same thing. I am only saying that it is still a crappy deal for the kids and the University. Honestly I would have had to take the job also but I would have at least tried to wait until the recruiting season was over. What difference does a couple of weeks make. He obviously was their #1 choice all along, so much that they pushed Seifert out to make room for him, so why not wait for Feb 7 to come and go. I am sure if Eddie D and Carmen wanted him that bad they could of kept it quiet for a few weeks. I guess all the preaching about commitment was abunch of bull and that all underclassmen should turn pro and help their families whatever. From a financail stanpoint hey you are the man, from the sporting standpoint you don't know jack. This is a bad move by the 49ers as you will soon see.<br>  First of all Im 20 years old and I will be a sports journalism major. So don't tell me that I don't know jack. You may have a pretty good point about the timeing on "Mooch's" decision but if you think about it, even if Cal recruited 6 or 7 studs I still think he would have left. He was in a terrible situation at Cal because Barnes couldn't have the extra year he wanted, Gonzalez is off to the NFL, and his defense ranked 108th in the country! I don't think Steve saw anything good comming his way in the immidiate future and in today's game you must win now! You must wounder why I'm so touchy about this situation, well I'm full blooded Italian and I bleed green and gold!!!! Go pack!!!<br>
<br>
