In Reply to: <a href="534.html">You still don't get it</a> posted by carlo on January 17, 1997 at 09:55:03:<p>
Now we are talking some sports Carlo. Cal is in a sorry state with or without Mariucci, all your points are valid and I honestly believe he should have taken the job. I just think he did the Bears no justice with the timing of his decision and all the crap he was spewing about not being interested in the pros a couple of weeks ago. I think you should be happy because now I think that the Pack will have an easier time beating up on the Niners in the years to come. I hope that you are from Wisconsin or at least remember the pre Don Majkowski era because I am sick of all the bandwagon Packer fans! All kidding aside though, the Pack are a great team and that is all good and fine I am just pissed because I think the Niners will live to regret this decision and Cal is hopeless without a sound offensive mind and the lure of NFL caliber coaching, they just can't get anyone to come their because their facilities blow.I hope you are not a Stanford fan as well.<br>
