Posted by carlo on January 17, 1997 at 15:17:57:<p>
In Reply to: <a href="536.html">Oh,now I see</a> posted by Chris on January 17, 1997 at 13:46:33:<p>
: Now we are talking some sports Carlo. Cal is in a sorry state with or without Mariucci, all your points are valid and I honestly believe he should have taken the job. I just think he did the Bears no justice with the timing of his decision and all the crap he was spewing about not being interested in the pros a couple of weeks ago. I think you should be happy because now I think that the Pack will have an easier time beating up on the Niners in the years to come. I hope that you are from Wisconsin or at least remember the pre Don Majkowski era because I am sick of all the bandwagon Packer fans! All kidding aside though, the Pack are a great team and that is all good and fine I am just pissed because I think the Niners will live to regret this decision and Cal is hopeless without a sound offensive mind and the lure of NFL caliber coaching, they just can't get anyone to come their because their facilities blow.I hope you are not a Stanford fan as well.<br>   Ok at least we have come to a conclusion on the "Mooch" discussion. Now I'll tell you how I became a Packer fan. It's funny that you brought up Don Majkowski because he was my idol when I was little. My room was coated with pics of him and Tony Mandarich. Im not from Wisconsin but I did go to Seattle this year and my friends and I saw them play the Seahawks. We stayed in the same hotel as them "Four Seasons" and we got pics with Reggie, Shawn Jones, Robert Brooks, Freeman, Koonce, Benett, etc. All of these guys were classy guys they all talked to us and laughed except for one guy, Frank Winters, he was an arrogant bastard. Anyways it is frustrating wearing my gear now because everyone thinks your on the wagon but as long as my family and friends and hundereds of people in the San Ramon area still look at me as the kid who's been wearing those ugly green clothes since 6th grade, that's fine with me! I do like Stanford too, football baseball and basketball.<br>Do you know of any other sites were you can voice your own oppinion? I just got  this computer and I am very illiterate. I want to talk sports 'till I drop!
<br>
