<center><center><a href="http://www.kron.com/sales/wells"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/ani6.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Wells Fargo Online Banking"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Gourmet Oatmeal



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



(Courtesy of Bradley Ogden)<p>



1 1/4 cups old-fashioned oats<br>

2 1/2 cups skim milk<br>

1/4 cup water <br>

3/4 cup dried fruit cut into 1/2 inch pieces<br>

1 tbs. maple syrup<br>

1/8 tsp. salt<br>

1 tbs. brown sugar, firmly packed<br>

pinch of cinnamon<p>



Soak the oats in 1 cup of the skim milk and the water overnight in the refrigerator. In a heavy-bottomed saucepan combine the oats with all the remaining ingredients. Bring to a slow boil over medium heat. Add to a double boiler and cover. Cook for 15 minutes, stirring often. Remove from the heat and let the oatmeal stand, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes before serving. <p>



Serving suggestions: Top each serving with 1 teaspoon butter (optional) and serve with warm milk and a sprinkle of cinnamon. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



