<HEAD>



<!-----------------------Begin Page Title--------------------------->



<TITLE> Light and Easy Pear-Cranberry Crisp</TITLE>



<!-----------------------End Page Title--------------------------->



</HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../../images/background.gif" LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<img src="../images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>



<img src="../../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br>



<img src="../../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://tours.excite.com"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/excite_found.gif" border=2 align=center alt="'Clicking', 'Found', and 'Search'"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Light and Easy Pear-Cranberry Crisp



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



Note: For accuracy all dry ingredients are given first by weight, and then by cup (volume) measure.  If you do not have a kitchen scale, use your liquid or dry cup measure.<p>



1 lb. firm pears, peeled and sliced<br>

5 oz. fresh cranberries  (about 1 cup) <br>

3 1/2  oz. granulated sugar (about 1/2 cup) combined with 2 tbs. flour<br>

3 1/2  oz. flour (about 3/4 cup) <br>

3 oz. brown sugar  (about 1/3 cup) <br>

3 oz. granulated sugar  (about 1/3 cup) <br>

1/4  tsp. sea salt<br>

1/4  tsp. ground cinnamon<br>

1/2  tsp. freshly grated ginger<br>

4 tbs. rice bran oil  (or other vegetable oil) <p>



Combine the pears and cranberries with the sugar-flour mixture. Transfer the fruit to a 9 or 10-inch baking dish. Combine the flour, sugars, salt, cinnamon, ginger and oil. Sprinkle evenly over the fruit.  Bake in a preheated 400 degree oven, approximately 30 minutes until the top is browned. <p>



Serve warm or at room temperature. Serves 8. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



