<img src="../../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://tours.excite.com/go.webx?128@@.ee6c02d/0"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/excite_banned.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Banned Books"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Roast Fish, Potatoes, & Artichokes



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



Courtesy of:<br>

Rose Pistola<br>

532 Columbus Avenue<br>

San Francisco, CA  94133<br>

(415) 399-0499<p>



One 1 to 1 1/2-pound fresh fish<br>

Salt<br>

Pepper<br>

1/4 cup olive oil  (preferably Ligroin or French) <br>

3/4 lb. thinly sliced potatoes, cooked<br>

5 thinly sliced raw baby artichokes (held in acidulated water) <br>

3 bay leaves<br>

1 large sprig fresh marjoram<br>

1/4  cup white wine<p>



Season fish with salt and pepper and place marjoram in the cavity. Toss potatoes, artichokes and bay leaves with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Put fish in an oval baking dish. Pour artichoke mixture over the top, tucking some of the potato artichoke slices under the fish. Pour white wine over all. <p>



Bake in a 550 degree oven until brown, crusty and fish is cooked through, about 15 to 20 minutes. Put on a platter with cooking juices and serve. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



</BLOCKQUOTE></td>



</tr>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



