<HTML>



<HEAD>



<!-----------------------Begin Page Title--------------------------->



<TITLE> Potato Gnocchi With Wild Mushrooms</TITLE>



<!-----------------------End Page Title--------------------------->



</HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../../images/background.gif" LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<img src="../images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>



<img src="../../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br>



<img src="../../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://www.kidsfirst.org/resource.html"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/kidsfirst2.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Click Here For Free Children's Health Information"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Potato Gnocchi With Wild Mushrooms



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



Courtesy of: <br>

Campton Place Hotel<br>

340 Stockton Street<br>

San Francisco, CA 94108<br>

(415) 781-5555<p>



Serves 6<p>



<b>Ingredients</b><br>

3  medium russet potatoes (or 24 oz. russets) <br>

1 1/2  egg yolks<br>

2  tsp. sweet butter, softened<br>

Salt, white pepper & freshly grated nutmeg to taste<br>

1 cup (approximately) all purpose flour plus extra for dusting<p>



<b>Equipment</b><br>

Flour sifter or large strainer<br>

Potato ricer or food mill<br>

Rolling pin<br>

Mixing bowl<br>

Rubber spatula<br>

Large chef's knife<br>

Nutmeg grater<p>



Preheat oven to 450 degrees.  Bake potatoes for approximately one hour or until very soft (bake on a thick layer of rock salt for even cooking). Remove from oven and immediately slice potatoes in half, lengthwise. Working with great care not to burn yourself, squeeze the skins to remove the potato's interior. Discard the skins.  While piping hot, immediately run the potato through a food mill or ricer into a mixing bowl.  Use the rubber spatula to mash the potatoes to a smooth puree, yet take care not to overwork the potatoes (gummy, gluey texture). <p>



Incorporate the butter well, and then thoroughly combine the yolks. Season with salt, white pepper and freshly grated nutmeg. Spread this mixture out onto a sheet pan (about 1" thick) and allow to cool to room temperature. Place the potato mixture back into a mixing bowl and sift about 3/4 to 1 cup of flour 

on top. Use a rubber spatula to "cut" the flour in; do not stir it in. When the mixture is crumbly, about the size of peas, gently knead the crumbles together enough to form a ball. <p>



Dust your work surface, gnocchi dough and rolling pin, lightly with flour. Roll the dough up and place seam side down, then repeat. Repeat this procedure just until the dough begins to become elastic, then stop. Roll the dough out to1/2-inch thick, then slice lengthwise into 1/2-inch strips. Roll these strips 

into logs. When all the dough has been rolled, align the logs together and cut into 3/4-inch pieces. Make an indentation into each piece and place on a sheet pan until ready to use. <p>



To Serve -- Drop gnocchies into gently boiling, lightly salted water. When they rise to the surface they are ready to be tossed into butter. <p>



<b>Mushroom Saut</b><p>



2   lbs. assorted wild mushrooms, cleaned and sliced<br>

Shaved or grated parmesan cheese<br>

1/4  cup vegetable oil<br>

Fresh cut chives<br>

4  tbs. butter<p>



Saut mushrooms in a medium hot pan with vegetable oil, season with salt and pepper. Place in a serving dish and top with the gnocchi. Sprinkle with cheese and chives.<p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



</BLOCKQUOTE></td>



</tr>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<a href="../kitchen.html"><img src="../../images/back.gif" width=82 height=36 border=0 vspace=2></a> <br>



</td>



<td valign=top><center><a href="../../home.html"><img src="../../images/nc4_header.gif" border=0 width=156 height=39></a> <br><br>



<hr>



<font size=2>Copyright &copy; 1996 <a href="http://www.kron.com"><b>KRON-TV</b></a>. All rights reserved.</font>



