<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://www.kron.com/sales/wells"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/ani6.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Wells Fargo Online Banking"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Salsa Roja & Roasted Tomato Guacamole



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



Courtesy of: <br>

Cafe Marimba<br>

2317 Chestnut Street<br>

San Francisco, CA  94123<br>

(415)  776-1506<p><br>



<b>Salsa Roja</b><p>



4-5 Roma tomatoes<br>

2  jalapenos  (stem removed) <br>

1/2 sliced onion<br>

10  small garlic cloves (peeled) <br>

Salt to taste<br>

3-4 tbs. water<p>



Roast tomatoes and jalapenos until very soft and partially charred on a  very hot cast iron pan.  Also do onions and garlic on same pan but on  slightly lower heat until light brown. Rough chop all ingredients with a sharp knife. Put in a bowl, add salt and water. Using a large spoon mix  and chop until flavors are blended. Taste and adjust seasonings. If you are making a larger amount you can use a food processor or blender by using the pulse button.  Be sure not to over blend.  Salsa should be  chunky, not smooth. Yields approximately 2 cups. <p>



<b>Roasted Tomato Guacamole</b><p>



3 ripe avocados<br>

3-4 small tomatoes<br>

3 rounded tbs. of chopped cilantro<br>

1-2  tbs. chopped fine jalapenos or serrano chiles<br>

Salt<p>



Under broiler on high heat, place tomatoes in a pan and roast them until soft and charred. Remove and cool. In a molecajete (lava stone bowl) or metal bowl place all ingredients, including salt. Mash and chop roughly all ingredients so that flavors come out. Be sure to leave it chunky, not pureed. Serves 4.<p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



</BLOCKQUOTE></td>



