<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://tours.excite.com"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/excite_found.gif" border=2 align=center alt="'Clicking', 'Found', and 'Search'"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Hummus  (Garbanzo Bean Dip)



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



1 can (15 1/2 oz) garbanzo beans (chick peas)<br>

1 clove garlic, peeled (more if you dare!) <br>

1/4 cup tahini (sesame seed paste) <br>

1/3 cup lemon juice<br>

1/4 teaspoon ground cumin<p>



Drain the garbanzo beans, rinse them under cold water and drain well. <p>



With the food processor running, drop the garlic clove through the feed tube. Process for 30 seconds, or until the garlic is finely chopped. <p>



Add the garbanzo beans and pulse several times. Add the tahini, lemon juice and cumin to the bean mixture and puree until the dip is smooth. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



