<center><center><a href="http://www.kidsfirst.org/resource.html"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/kidsfirst2.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Click Here For Free Children's Health Information"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Mexican Won Tons



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



(Courtesy of Paula Hamilton)<p>



12 won ton wrappers<br>

4 oz. hot pepper jack cheese<br>

1/2 small ripe avocado<br>

1 teaspoon lemon juice<br>

1/8 teaspoon salt<br>

12 leaves fresh cilantro<p>



Preheat oven to 425 F.  Press a won ton wrapper into each of 12 miniature muffin tins. Cut the cheese into 12 (3/4-inch) cubes and place one cube of cheese in each pastry cup. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, until the cheese melts and the pastry is golden brown and crisp. <p>



Meanwhile, peel the avocado and mash the flesh with a fork. Stir in the lemon juice and salt. When the won tons are done, move them to a serving tray and top each with a dollop of guacamole and a cilantro leaf. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



