</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://www.kron.com/sales/wells"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/ani6.gif" border=2 align=center alt="Wells Fargo Online Banking"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Smoked Fish Spread



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



1/2 pound smoked trout or cod fillets<br>

   1 container (8 oz.) whipped cream cheese<br>

   1 half teaspoon lemon juice<br>

   1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon prepared white horseradish<br>

   4 green onions<p>



Remove the skin from the fish. Place the fish in a food processor. Pulse several times to chop. Add the cream cheese, lemon juice and horseradish and process about 30 seconds longer until the mixture is well combined.<p>



Cut the root ends off the green onions and finely slice them. Add the onions to the smoked fish mixture and process several seconds, just until they are mixed in.<p>



Serve immediately with crackers or refrigerate to serve later.<p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



