</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://www.atplay.com/"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/atplaybannerkron.gif" border=2 align=center alt="@PLAY Ski Directory"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H2>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Tonos Me Orzo<br>

Seared Ahi Tuna with Orzo Salad & Dalmata



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H2></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



(Courtesy of Chef Peter Casartelli)<p>



<b>Tuna</b><p>



6 oz. ahi tuna<p>



Marinade:<br>

   1 tbs. green onions<br>

   1 tsp. basil<br>

   1 tsp. oregano<br>

1/2 tsp. lemon zest<br>

1/2 cup pure olive oil<p>



<b>Dalmata (Caper Salsa)</b><p>



   2 Roman tomatoes (seeded & diced)<br> 

   4  tbs. calamata olives (pitted)<br>

1/2 cup red onion (diced)<br>

1/2 cup eggplant (roasted) <br>

   2 green onions (chopped)<br>

   4 tbs. lemon juice<br>

   6 basil leaves (chopped) <br>

3/4 cup extra virgin olive oil<br>

   4 tbs. capers<br>

Salt & pepper to taste<p>



Toss all ingredients and set aside.<p>



<b>Orzo Salad</b><p>



1/2 cup orzo pasta<br>

1/4 cup water<br>

1/2 cup pure olive oil<br>

   4 tbs. white wine vinegar<br>

Fresh Italian parsley (whole leaves)<br>

Fresh basil (whole leaves)<br>

Salt & pepper to taste<p>



Cook orzo pasta according to directions on the box. Strain and cool under cold water. Add a little olive oil so it does not stick. Set aside. In a blender blend together the water, parsley and basil.  Place pasta in a bowl and add vinegar, blended herbs, olive oil and salt and pepper to taste. <p>



<b>Serving Directions</b><p>



Heat saut pan and add one tablespoon of cooking oil. Salt and pepper each side of tuna and sear in the pan on each side until medium rare. Set aside to rest. <p>



Place cold orzo salad on center of plate. Slice tuna against grain in 1/4-inch slices, fan over orzo. Spoon dalmata (caper salsa) over top. Garnish with sprig of Italian parsley. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



