<HEAD>



<!-----------------------Begin Page Title--------------------------->



<TITLE> Fleur de Lys' Chocolate Truffles </TITLE>



<!-----------------------End Page Title--------------------------->



</HEAD>



<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" BACKGROUND="../../images/background.gif"

LINK="#151bd4" VLINK="#496973" ALINK="#ff0707">



<table align=left  border=0>



<tr>



<td valign=top>



<img src="../images/header.jpeg" width=117 height=129 border=0><br>



<img src="../../images/nc4_grey.gif" width=111 height=24 align=bottom> 



<br>



<img src="../../images/greydot.gif" width=150  height=1>



<br><br>



</td>



<td valign=top>



<center><center><a href="http://www.atplay.com/"><img src="http://www.kron.com/sales/ads/atplaybannerkron.gif" border=2 align=center alt="@PLAY Ski Directory"></center></a>
</center></a>



<HR>



<blockquote>



<H1>



<!-----------------------Begin Story Title--------------------------->



Fleur de Lys' Chocolate Truffles 



<!-----------------------End Story Title--------------------------->



</H1></blockquote> <blockquote>



<!-----------------------Begin Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------End Picture--------------------------->



<!-----------------------Begin Story--------------------------->



1 3/4  cups cream<br>

1/4  cup honey<br>

1  lb. bittersweet chocolate cut into quarter-inch pieces<br>

7  tbs. butter at room temperature<br>

2  tbs.  dark or light rum<br>

1/2  cup unsweetened cocoa powder<p>



Place the cream and honey in a saucepan and bring to a boil stirring occasionally. 

Remove from heat and stir in the chocolate.  Cover and let the mixture stand for five

minutes.  Whisk in the butter one tablespoon at a time until smooth.  Transfer the

mixture to a small mixing bowl and stir in the rum.  Let cool for 30 minutes then

refrigerate for an hour-and-a-half. <p>



Using a small ice cream scoop or a large melon baller, scoop out one-inch balls and

place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or aluminum foil.  Refrigerate for

15 minutes.  Place the cocoa in a shallow dish and roll the chocolate balls one at a

time in the cocoa until completely covered.  (Don't worry if the truffles are

irregular in shape and size - it will only look more authentic). Serve the truffles

in fluted paper candy cups. <p>



<i>NOTE</i>: You can roll the truffles in a variety of coatings. For example, chopped

pistachios, toasted hazelnuts, toasted almonds, shredded coconut.  Make sure to chop

the nuts into small pieces.  Feel free to substitute Grand Marnier, Cognac or your

favorite liqueur for the rum in the recipe. Do not add liqueur if serving to

children. <p>



Makes about 3 dozen. <p>



<!-----------------------End Story --------------------------->



<B> <I>



<!-----------------------Begin Copyright--------------------------->





<!-----------------------End Copyright--------------------------->



</I></B>



</BLOCKQUOTE></td>



</tr>



